"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pullrequests/42.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pull-requests/42"}}, "title": "Scrolling dragdroptabs"}, "content": {"raw": "The odd behavior seems to be fixed and scrolling behaves much nicer. \n\nThanks!", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The odd behavior seems to be fixed and scrolling behaves much nicer. </p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-04-03T06:52:38.652721+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jan Werkmann", "uuid": "{44c4905c-2b90-4045-a5f1-652b8e228626}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B44c4905c-2b90-4045-a5f1-652b8e228626%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B44c4905c-2b90-4045-a5f1-652b8e228626%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:a70cc9cf-684e-4849-a61a-9ade4d7218b5/07e5095a-4741-4dc0-a462-9c7d455f961d/128"}}, "nickname": "PhyNerd", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:a70cc9cf-684e-4849-a61a-9ade4d7218b5"}, "updated_on": "2018-04-03T06:52:38.707765+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 60468154}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 42, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pullrequests/42.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pull-requests/42"}}, "title": "Scrolling dragdroptabs"}}, {"update": {"description": "Allow dragdroptabs to have scroll buttons, and use them by default.\r\n\r\nThis restores the old behaviour which allows you to have larger numbers of tabs with scrolling rather than the text being elided in the tab labels.\r\n\r\n![scroll_buttons.png](https://bitbucket.org/repo/KEMMje/images/4017131629-scroll_buttons.png)", "title": "Scrolling dragdroptabs", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "8b26cae78bce", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/commit/8b26cae78bce.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/commits/8b26cae78bce"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/labscript_utils.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{68347210-fb1e-4b58-86c0-bd2c04396e63}ts=249922"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "labscript_utils", "full_name": "labscript_suite/labscript_utils", "uuid": "{68347210-fb1e-4b58-86c0-bd2c04396e63}"}, "branch": {"name": "default"}}, "reason": "", "source": {"commit": {"hash": "5cc2a482f6d7", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/cbillington/labscript_utils/commit/5cc2a482f6d7"}, "html": {"href": "#!/cbillington/labscript_utils/commits/5cc2a482f6d7"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/cbillington/labscript_utils"}, "html": {"href": "#!/cbillington/labscript_utils"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{455d0b5d-4852-4e4a-b8b1-f5ba77882210}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "labscript_utils", "full_name": "cbillington/labscript_utils", "uuid": "{455d0b5d-4852-4e4a-b8b1-f5ba77882210}"}, "branch": {"name": "scrolling-tabs"}}, "state": "OPEN", "author": {"display_name": "Chris Billington", "uuid": "{e363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9238baf7300c41c0e7294db922899e6ad=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCB-1.png"}}, "nickname": "cbillington", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cbf1bc43-1dc2-477b-9e25-1a8f40fd7ee3"}, "date": "2018-04-03T02:30:40.991834+00:00"}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 42, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pullrequests/42.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pull-requests/42"}}, "title": "Scrolling dragdroptabs"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pullrequests/42/comments/60456204.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pull-requests/42/_/diff#comment-60456204"}}, "parent": {"id": 60284316, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pullrequests/42/comments/60284316.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pull-requests/42/_/diff#comment-60284316"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 42, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pullrequests/42.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pull-requests/42"}}, "title": "Scrolling dragdroptabs"}, "content": {"raw": "Thanks!\n\nI can easily make it scroll one tab-width, which seems sensible (and is what Qt itself does). I wouldn't make it completely flush (otherwise it looks visibly like there are no more tabs - i.e. that you are scrolled all the way to one side), but with a few pixel gap the same way it currently does for when you focus a new tab.\n\nThe buttons appearing when they shouldn't may be fixed in the most recent commit. This may have been because the tab bar size and its container's size are not the same in macos (presumably because of the centring of the tabs), whereas they are the same in linux and windows. It now uses the width of the container to decide whether it needs to put scroll buttons in. This makes no difference on Windows and linux but hopefully fixes your problem.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Thanks!</p>\n<p>I can easily make it scroll one tab-width, which seems sensible (and is what Qt itself does). I wouldn't make it completely flush (otherwise it looks visibly like there are no more tabs - i.e. that you are scrolled all the way to one side), but with a few pixel gap the same way it currently does for when you focus a new tab.</p>\n<p>The buttons appearing when they shouldn't may be fixed in the most recent commit. This may have been because the tab bar size and its container's size are not the same in macos (presumably because of the centring of the tabs), whereas they are the same in linux and windows. It now uses the width of the container to decide whether it needs to put scroll buttons in. This makes no difference on Windows and linux but hopefully fixes your problem.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-04-03T02:21:54.931877+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Chris Billington", "uuid": "{e363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Be363c5a9-5075-4656-afb5-88bd6a6dceeb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9238baf7300c41c0e7294db922899e6ad=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCB-1.png"}}, "nickname": "cbillington", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cbf1bc43-1dc2-477b-9e25-1a8f40fd7ee3"}, "updated_on": "2018-04-03T02:21:54.935104+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 60456204}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 42, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pullrequests/42.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pull-requests/42"}}, "title": "Scrolling dragdroptabs"}}, {"update": {"description": "Allow dragdroptabs to have scroll buttons, and use them by default.\r\n\r\nThis restores the old behaviour which allows you to have larger numbers of tabs with scrolling rather than the text being elided in the tab labels.\r\n\r\n![scroll_buttons.png](https://bitbucket.org/repo/KEMMje/images/4017131629-scroll_buttons.png)", "title": "Scrolling dragdroptabs", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "8b26cae78bce", "type": "commit", "links": {